The paper deals with data structures and algorithms for representing and manipulating metric spaces that can be embedded in the plane, specifically the Manhattan plane. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the construction of tight spans, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper mentions applications in testing for isometric embeddings, which could fall under computational complexity (cs.CC) or signal processing (cs.SI).
